channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

2020 presidential candidate's spouse wins primary for David Trone's Maryland House seat
item.description: April McClain-Delaney, wife of ex-2020 presidential candidate John Delaney, has won the Democratic nomination for Maryland's 6th Congressional District.

item.title: China: 'Bullying' Tariff Hike Shows Biden, US 'Losing Their Minds'
item.description: The U.S. move to raise tariffs on Chinese goods is a case of "typical bullying" and "shows that some people in the United States have reached the point of losing their minds," China's foreign minister said Wednesday.

item.title: House Republican demands Garland appoint special counsel to investigate Biden over stalled Israel aid
item.description: Rep. Claudia Tenney, R-N.Y., asked the Justice Department to appoint a special counsel to investigate and possible prosecute President Biden over delayed military aid to Israel.

item.title: Election Polls Not 'Infallible Predictors,' Should Be Viewed With 'Caution'
item.description: Even though a spate of polls shows former President Donald Trump leading President Joe Biden in key battleground states that are expected to help decide the outcome of the 2024 presidential election, campaign experts say the voter surveys should be "taken with a grain of...

item.title: Biden's Brain Breaks at APAICS Gala, Makes Creepy Comment About Woman, Adds New 'Origin Story'
Game on as Republicans aim to flip heavily blue state Senate seat in push to regain majority
item.description: Former two-term Republican Gov. Larry Hogan of Maryland wins the state's 2024 GOP Senate primary. His party aims to flip a longtime Democratic-held seat in the blue state.

item.title: Ipsos Poll: Trump, Biden in Nationwide Dead Heat
item.description: President Joe Biden and Republican challenger Donald Trump are tied in the race to win the November presidential election, as Trump fights criminal prosecution and Biden weathers criticism over his support for Israel's war against Hamas terrorists.

item.title: Tuesday at Trump's Trial - Cohen Cross-Examined (Trump Trial - Day 17)
Biden aides fear president may be too worried to do his job after Hunter Biden trial begins: report
item.description: President Biden worries about Hunter Biden every day, and he could become majorly distracted by the issue when his son's trial begins in June, aides say.

item.title: Can Fmr Gov. Hogan Pick Up Maryland Senate Seat for GOP?
item.description: Speculation soon arose after networks projected that Prince George County Executive Angela Alsobrooks as the winner of Maryland's Democratic U.S. Senate primary late Tuesday evening.

item.title: SUPER CRINGE: Blinken Joins Ukrainian Band in Kiev to Butcher Neil Young's 'Rockin' in the Free World'
'Child predator': Illegal immigrant with past sex conviction captured in border state
item.description: An illegal immigrant described by officials as a "child predator" was arrested at the southern border in Arizona last week, Border Patrol announced.

item.title: Christina Bobb to Newsmax: Defense Could Rest After Prosecution's Case
item.description: Republican National Committee attorney Christina Bobb voiced uncertainty Tuesday on whether former President Donald Trump's defense team would present a rebuttal case as the business records trial in Manhattan enters its fifth week on 34 felony counts.
